726634f-b.title: Queens: 114th Street - 38th Avenue
726634f-b.text:
Flushing Meadow Park (Queens): At the north end of the
park, near the mouth of the Flushing River. View 2 shows W.P.A.
workmen cutting pampas grass at 114th Street and 38th Avenue,
and view 3 the north end of the park being improved for the 1939-
40 World's Fair.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: September 29, 1935
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 2: October 4, 1935
View 3: June 16, 1937

725806f-a.text:
114th Street, north froa 38th Avenue. The area on the right
will later become part of the New York World's Fair Grounds of
